misconceptions.inferred_category_name: No misconception detected (correct conditional range mapping)
misconceptions.student_thought_process: The student believes that checking the grade from highest range to lowest with an if/else-if chain will correctly select exactly one letter grade and then print it.
misconceptions.conceptual_gap: No gap: Java evaluates the if/else-if chain top-down, takes the first true branch, assigns the char, and then prints it. The numeric ranges are correctly covered by the comparisons (>=90, >=80, >=70, >=60, else).
misconceptions.error_manifestation: None (produces correct output for all integer inputs 0–100).
